Basic histogram

library(ggplot2)
 
data <- data.frame(value=rnorm(100))

head(data)
##        value
## 1 -1.1802521
## 2  0.4098730
## 3 -0.4040435
## 4 -0.1694725
## 5  0.6378890
## 6 -0.2339533

# basic histogram
ggplot(data, aes(x=value)) + 
  geom_histogram()

Control bin size

# Libraries
library(tidyverse)
library(hrbrthemes)

# Load dataset
data <- read.table("../data/1_OneNum.csv", header=TRUE) %>%
  filter(price<300)

head(data)
##   price
## 1    75
## 2   104
## 3    92
## 4    64
## 5   265
## 6    35

ggplot(data, aes(x=price)) +
  geom_histogram( binwidth=3, fill="#69b3a2", color="#e9ecef", alpha=0.9) +
  ggtitle("Bin size = 3") +
  theme_ipsum() +
  theme(
    plot.title = element_text(size=15)
  )

Mirror histogram

library(ggplot2)
library(hrbrthemes)

data <- data.frame(
  var1 = rnorm(1000),
  var2 = rnorm(1000, mean=2)
)

head(data)
##         var1     var2
## 1  1.3394677 2.597375
## 2 -0.4768819 2.193712
## 3 -0.7636468 2.270278
## 4 -0.5980124 2.212953
## 5  1.0144181 3.813173
## 6 -1.2010998 3.259457

ggplot(data, aes(x=x) ) +
  geom_histogram( aes(x = var1, y = ..density..), fill="#69b3a2" ) +
  geom_label( aes(x=4.5, y=0.25, label="variable1"), color="#69b3a2") +
  geom_histogram( aes(x = var2, y = -..density..), fill= "#404080") +
  geom_label( aes(x=4.5, y=-0.25, label="variable2"), color="#404080") +
  theme_ipsum() +
  xlab("value of x")

Several histograms on the same axis

library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr)
library(hrbrthemes)

# Build dataset with different distributions
data <- data.frame(
  type = c( rep("variable 1", 1000), rep("variable 2", 1000) ),
  value = c( rnorm(1000), rnorm(1000, mean=4) )
)

head(data)
##         type      value
## 1 variable 1 -0.9348002
## 2 variable 1 -2.3464811
## 3 variable 1  0.8494634
## 4 variable 1  0.3883706
## 5 variable 1 -2.6720447
## 6 variable 1  0.3252224

ggplot(data, aes(x=value, fill=type)) +
  geom_histogram( color="#e9ecef", alpha=0.6, position = 'identity') +
  scale_fill_manual(values=c("#69b3a2", "#404080")) +
  theme_ipsum() +
  labs(fill="")

Using small multiple

library(tidyverse)
library(hrbrthemes)
library(viridis)
library(forcats)

data <- read.table("../data/probly.csv", header=TRUE, sep=",") %>%
  gather(key="text", value="value") %>%
  mutate(text = gsub("\\.", " ",text)) %>%
  mutate(value = round(as.numeric(value),0)) %>% 
  mutate(text = fct_reorder(text, value))

head(data)
##               text value
## 1 Almost Certainly    95
## 2 Almost Certainly    95
## 3 Almost Certainly    95
## 4 Almost Certainly    95
## 5 Almost Certainly    98
## 6 Almost Certainly    95

ggplot(data, aes(x=value, color=text, fill=text)) +
  geom_histogram(alpha=0.6, binwidth = 5) +
  scale_fill_viridis(discrete=TRUE) + scale_color_viridis(discrete=TRUE) +
  theme_ipsum() +
  theme(legend.position="none", panel.spacing = unit(0.1, "lines"), 
        strip.text.x = element_text(size = 8)) +
  xlab("") + ylab("Assigned Probability (%)") +
  facet_wrap(~text)
